From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 29 Nov 2025 08:33:14 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: cix: Add CIX Sky1 SoC and Radxa Orion O6 device
 tree

Add device tree support for CIX Sky1 SoC and Radxa Orion O6 board,
porting from vendor kernel 6.6 to mainline 6.18-rc7.

Device tree changes:
- sky1.dtsi: Full SoC description with all peripherals
- sky1-orion-o6.dts: Radxa Orion O6 board configuration
- GIC: #interrupt-cells changed from 3 to 4 for GICv3
- Root interrupt-parent changed from &pdc to &gic
- All GIC interrupt specifiers updated to 4-cell format
- Mailbox nodes: reg addresses fixed (offset 0x80 after shmem)
- Mailbox nodes: cix,mbox_dir property (underscore, u32)
- SCMI: Both SMC and mailbox transport nodes configured
- GPIO: All s5 and FCH GPIO controllers enabled
- Regulators: Properly wired to GPIO controllers

DT binding headers added:
- clock/sky1-clk.h, sky1-audss.h
- power/sky1-power.h
- reset/sky1-reset.h, sky1-reset-fch.h, sky1-reset-audss.h
- pinctrl/pads-sky1.h
- phy/phy-cadence-torrent.h
- thermal/sky1-thermal.h

Driver stubs and Kconfig entries added for:
- PCIe Sky1 host controller
- PHY (Cadence Torrent, combo PHY)
- Pinctrl Sky1
- PWM Sky1
- Reset Sky1
- USB CDNS3 Sky1 glue
- Watchdog Sky1

Debug modifications to SCMI shmem, SMC transport, GIC, and
CIX mailbox drivers for boot debugging.

Current state: SCMI mailbox transport blocked by firmware
security firewall; SMC SCMI transport works with current BIOS.

Tested on Radxa Orion O6 with CIX Sky1 SoC, BIOS 1.0.0-5.
